textBeforeTable: Board of Certification Examination Passing Rate The Keene State College Athletic Training Program is accredited by CAATE (Commission on Accreditation of Athletic Training Education). Students who graduate with a degree in Athletic Training are eligible to take the BOC (Board of Certification) Athletic Training Certification Examination. The program prepares students for athletic training positions in educational, professional sport, military/law enforcement training, performing arts and clinical settings, as well as for graduate programs in Sports Medicine/Athletic Training, Exercise Physiology and Biomechanics or other Medical and Allied Health fields.
